children.text: There are top plate joints that have not been properly connected.
It is a requirement of AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction, clause 6.2.2.4 Joints in top plates and ring beams, that
‘Top plates and ring beams shall be joined using one of the methods, as appropriate, given in Section 9 for the relevant wind classification’ .
These top plates must be jointed using one of the methods outlined in AS 1684.
